text.tspan: Gross vs. net enrolment rate in primary education, 2019
Gross enrolment counts all children in primary school regardless of age, while net enrolment considers only those of
official primary age. Both are relative to the primary age group population.
Data source: UNESCO Institute for Statistics via World Bank (2023)
Note: Gross enrolment rate can surpass 100% when including students outside the official age due to early or late admissions and grade
